Page 51.

798
01:13:26,080 --> 01:13:27,600
[DO YOU

799
01:13:27,640 --> 01:13:29,400
WANT

800
01:13:29,440 --> 01:13:31,800
TO MEET ME?]

801
01:15:05,800 --> 01:15:08,520
Listen to this. "A boy of six,

802
01:15:08,560 --> 01:15:10,640
while his parents sleep, drives off

803
01:15:10,680 --> 01:15:12,360
in a pedal car.

804
01:15:12,400 --> 01:15:15,960
Found on a motorway near Münster in Germany,

805
01:15:16,000 --> 01:15:19,440
he told the police he wanted to see the stars."

806
01:15:19,480 --> 01:15:23,000
Isn't life beautiful, eh?

807
01:15:23,040 --> 01:15:27,440
Love. The only bug she hadn't caught!

808
01:15:27,480 --> 01:15:30,400
- Nobody's immune. - At least it gives me a break.

809
01:15:30,440 --> 01:15:32,560
Love's a great beautician.

810
01:15:34,680 --> 01:15:38,000
What's she like? Tall? Small? Blonde? Dark?

811
01:15:40,320 --> 01:15:42,320
Let's say... average height.

812
01:15:43,520 --> 01:15:46,440
Not a dwarf or a giraffe. Normal.

813
01:15:47,760 --> 01:15:49,920
Pretty, for her type.

814
01:15:49,960 --> 01:15:52,200
As for blonde or dark...

815
01:15:53,720 --> 01:15:56,680
...it's hard to say, but she wasn't a redhead.

816
01:15:56,720 --> 01:15:58,520
- Unless... - Forget it.

817
01:15:59,600 --> 01:16:04,280
I do remember she casually asked if you had a girlfriend.

818
01:16:04,320 --> 01:16:05,320
And?

819
01:16:05,360 --> 01:16:07,720
I said you weren't interested, right?

820
01:16:09,080 --> 01:16:10,520
You didn't!

821
01:16:10,560 --> 01:16:12,720
What do you care? You don't even know her.

822
01:16:13,720 --> 01:16:17,760
- Exactly. It's the mystery. - You won't find mystery here.

823
01:16:17,800 --> 01:16:19,920
A pound of nectarines, please.

824
01:16:19,960 --> 01:16:22,680
These ones here are the prettiest.

825
01:16:22,720 --> 01:16:24,760
Trust him. He's an artist!

826
01:16:24,800 --> 01:16:27,760
He's been going home every night with tons of unsold stock.

827
01:16:27,800 --> 01:16:30,840
What for? Is he stewing a pig?

828
01:16:30,880 --> 01:16:32,960
No, sir! He's studying art!

829
01:16:33,000 --> 01:16:36,560
He sells leeks all day long and paints turnips all night!

830
01:16:36,600 --> 01:16:38,600
The boy's a useless vegetable.

831
01:16:38,640 --> 01:16:40,080
A good prompter

832
01:16:40,120 --> 01:16:43,560
in each cellar window whispering cutting retorts

833
01:16:43,600 --> 01:16:46,120
would mean shy people had the last laugh.

834
01:16:46,160 --> 01:16:48,520
At least you'll never be a vegetable.

835
01:16:48,560 --> 01:16:50,720
Even artichokes

836
01:16:50,760 --> 01:16:51,760
have hearts.

837
01:16:54,640 --> 01:16:58,120
You'll never be a vegetable. Even artichokes have hearts!

838
01:17:37,840 --> 01:17:39,360
Memory seven.

839
01:17:56,360 --> 01:18:00,440
Darling Mado, I miss you more and more each day.

840
01:18:00,480 --> 01:18:03,640
I'm an exile in a world of dreary khaki.

841
01:18:03,680 --> 01:18:05,880
I can't sleep, can't eat...

842
01:18:05,920 --> 01:18:08,520
This camp was the biggest mistake of my life,

843
01:18:08,560 --> 01:18:12,200
depriving me of my beloved for five long weeks.

844
01:18:12,240 --> 01:18:15,000
I think of you endlessly. Your Adrien.

845
01:18:16,680 --> 01:18:21,280
I turned down my last month's wages instead of giving notice.

846
01:18:22,280 --> 01:18:25,480
I dream of better times ahead.

847
01:18:25,520 --> 01:18:29,360
An orange-colored day. Remember, my love?

848
01:18:29,400 --> 01:18:31,400
Your ever-loving Adrien.

849
01:18:33,120 --> 01:18:34,480
Good news, darling Mado.

850
01:18:34,520 --> 01:18:37,720
Soon I'll be able to afford a car

851
01:18:37,760 --> 01:18:40,160
and drive home every night.

852
01:18:40,200 --> 01:18:44,440
Till then, meet me on Friday and we'll go out.

853
01:21:29,400 --> 01:21:31,400
Psychiatric Helpline.

854
01:21:32,880 --> 01:21:34,880
Hello? Hello?

855
01:22:14,120 --> 01:22:16,480
One hour later at 11 Boulevard St Martin,

856
01:22:16,520 --> 01:22:20,000
Amélie walks into a party goods and costume shop.

857
01:22:21,000 --> 01:22:25,280
At the same time, a man leaves his home at 108 Rue Lecourbe.

858
01:22:27,120 --> 01:22:30,760
26 minutes later, Amélie is at the photo booth at the Gare de l'Est.

859
01:22:34,840 --> 01:22:38,760
Simultaneously, the man in red shoes parks outside.

860
01:22:38,800 --> 01:22:42,040
The time is exactly 11:40.

861
01:23:25,840 --> 01:23:27,760
At this precise moment,

862
01:23:27,880 --> 01:23:32,400
only Amélie has the key to the riddle of the mystery man.

863
01:23:37,120 --> 01:23:38,720
How's it going, Mrs. Wells?

864
01:23:38,800 --> 01:23:41,520
It's always better when it's not raining.

865
01:23:41,560 --> 01:23:43,880
- This is for you. - Me?

866
01:23:53,440 --> 01:23:56,960
Dear Mrs. Wells, We recently recovered a mailbag

867
01:23:57,040 --> 01:23:59,000
that was lost in a plane crash

868
01:23:59,080 --> 01:24:02,560
on October 12th 1969 on Mont Blanc.

869
01:24:02,640 --> 01:24:06,880
We are forwarding the enclosed letter to your address.

870
01:24:06,960 --> 01:24:10,920
Please accept our apologies for the uncustomary delay.

871
01:24:11,000 --> 01:24:13,560
Jacques Grosjean, Customer Services.

872
01:24:14,840 --> 01:24:19,000
Darling Mado, I'm in exile. I can't sleep, can't eat.

873
01:24:19,040 --> 01:24:20,680
I think of you endlessly.

874
01:24:20,760 --> 01:24:24,440
I know I've made the biggest mistake of my life.

875
01:24:24,520 --> 01:24:27,080
I turned down that woman's money.

876
01:24:27,160 --> 01:24:31,880
If all goes well, I'll soon be able to afford a house.

877
01:24:31,920 --> 01:24:34,840
I dream of better times ahead

878
01:24:34,920 --> 01:24:38,600
when you'll forgive me and join me here

879
01:24:38,680 --> 01:24:41,880
one orange-colored day. Your ever-loving Adrien.

880
01:25:10,520 --> 01:25:12,560
Mr. Dufayel, another package for you.

881
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:25,080
Mr. Dufayel, do you know what happened to the concierge?

882
01:25:26,480 --> 01:25:27,760
She got a letter.

883
01:25:28,760 --> 01:25:31,480
From her husband. 40 years late.

884
01:25:33,720 --> 01:25:35,680
That's a lot, isn't it, Mr. Dufayel?

885
01:25:48,400 --> 01:25:51,680
I'm not big on still life, Mr. Dufayel.

886
01:25:51,760 --> 01:25:54,640
Then work on your thin layer.

887
01:25:54,680 --> 01:25:57,320
Fat over thin. Always!

888
01:26:15,400 --> 01:26:17,120
- Mr. Dufayel... - Yes!

889
01:26:17,160 --> 01:26:21,360
The papers said that there'll soon be a new star.

890
01:26:21,400 --> 01:26:28,240
- So you're into stars now? - I saw it on TV at my mum's, that's why.

891
01:26:30,000 --> 01:26:31,680
I don't know if it's true.

892
01:26:31,720 --> 01:26:33,920
In America

893
01:26:34,000 --> 01:26:37,160
they're going to take all the rich people's ashes,

894
01:26:37,200 --> 01:26:39,760
put them in a satellite

895
01:26:39,760 --> 01:26:42,000
and shoot it into space.

896
01:26:42,080 --> 01:26:44,360
The satellite's going to shine forever.

897
01:26:48,800 --> 01:26:50,280
And Lady Di...

898
01:26:50,320 --> 01:26:52,480
Will they do the same for her?

899
01:26:52,520 --> 01:26:53,480
Lady Di, Lady Di!

900
01:26:53,560 --> 01:26:54,760
Give it a rest!

901
01:26:54,760 --> 01:26:57,440
I can't concentrate.

902
01:26:59,520 --> 01:27:00,480
Lady Di!

903
01:27:01,560 --> 01:27:02,480
Lady Di!

904
01:27:03,720 --> 01:27:04,720
Renoir.

905
01:28:41,880 --> 01:28:42,880
Morning, sir.

906
01:28:58,920 --> 01:28:59,920
Cambodia.

907
01:29:05,280 --> 01:29:06,960
I don't understand.

908
01:29:07,000 --> 01:29:10,720
Brilliant! You couldn't have done better.

909
01:29:10,760 --> 01:29:13,840
- Did it work? - It's getting there.

910
01:29:13,840 --> 01:29:16,640
Ask me again any time. The harm's done.

911
01:29:16,720 --> 01:29:20,240
- What do you mean? - Everybody calls me Snow White!

912
01:30:32,240 --> 01:30:34,080
- Eva? - Yes?

913
01:30:34,120 --> 01:30:37,680
Could you stand in for me at four?

914
01:30:37,760 --> 01:30:39,600
Again?

915
01:30:42,800 --> 01:30:44,200
Close the door!

916
01:30:46,280 --> 01:30:48,200
What's up with him?

917
01:30:48,200 --> 01:30:49,920
Is he sulking?

918
01:30:49,960 --> 01:30:53,360
- He thinks I smile too much. - He'd rather you frowned?

919
01:30:53,440 --> 01:30:56,240
With other men, yes.

920
01:30:58,840 --> 01:31:03,080
Nino is late. Amélie can only think of two possible explanations.

921
01:31:03,120 --> 01:31:05,120
Firstly, that he didn't find the photo.

922
01:31:06,880 --> 01:31:09,240
Secondly, before he could assemble it,

923
01:31:09,280 --> 01:31:13,400
a gang of bank robbers took him hostage.

924
01:31:13,440 --> 01:31:15,360
The cops gave chase.

925
01:31:15,360 --> 01:31:17,120
They got away,

926
01:31:17,160 --> 01:31:19,800
but he caused a crash.

927
01:31:19,800 --> 01:31:21,920
When he came to,

928
01:31:22,000 --> 01:31:23,560
he'd lost his memory,

929
01:31:25,400 --> 01:31:27,200
An ex-con picked him up,

930
01:31:27,240 --> 01:31:31,280
mistook him for a fugitive, and shipped him to Istanbul.

931
01:31:32,200 --> 01:31:34,320
He met some Afghan raiders,

932
01:31:34,400 --> 01:31:37,840
who took him to steal some Russian warheads.

933
01:31:41,320 --> 01:31:45,000
But their truck hit a mine at the border with Tajikistan.

934
01:31:45,040 --> 01:31:50,320
He survived, took to the hills, and became a Mujaheddin.

935
01:31:50,360 --> 01:31:53,200
Amélie refuses to get upset for a guy

936
01:31:53,240 --> 01:31:57,640
who'll eat borscht all his life in a hat like a tea cosy.

937
01:32:16,080 --> 01:32:18,200
- What can I get you? - A coffee, please.

938
01:32:19,240 --> 01:32:21,040
A coffee.

939
01:32:42,160 --> 01:32:43,560
Here's your coffee.

940
01:32:45,040 --> 01:32:46,040
Thank you.

941
01:33:19,640 --> 01:33:21,040
He's understood.

942
01:33:21,080 --> 01:33:24,120
He's going to put his teaspoon down,

943
01:33:25,520 --> 01:33:28,960
dip his finger in the sugar,

944
01:33:33,520 --> 01:33:36,080
turn around slowly,

945
01:33:36,160 --> 01:33:38,160
and speak to me.

946
01:33:43,520 --> 01:33:45,440
Excuse me.

947
01:33:46,840 --> 01:33:48,040
Is this you?

948
01:33:54,280 --> 01:33:55,480
Yes, it's you.

949
01:34:15,320 --> 01:34:17,280
I'll take that.

950
01:34:19,640 --> 01:34:21,240
Another coffee?

951
01:34:21,280 --> 01:34:23,320
- No, thanks. I'm fine. - OK.

952
01:34:43,040 --> 01:34:47,280
So it's this man here, the one with his hand up?

953
01:34:48,520 --> 01:34:49,520
Yes.

954
01:34:51,720 --> 01:34:54,520
Is she in love with him?

955
01:34:57,200 --> 01:34:58,200
Yes.

956
01:35:00,040 --> 01:35:03,280
I think it's time she took a real risk.

957
01:35:03,320 --> 01:35:07,640
She might just do that. She's devising a stratagem.

958
01:35:07,640 --> 01:35:11,160
She's fond of stratagems.

959
01:35:13,160 --> 01:35:14,160
Yes.

960
01:35:15,800 --> 01:35:17,840
In fact, she's cowardly.

961
01:35:19,120 --> 01:35:22,360
That's why I can't capture her look.

962
01:35:24,160 --> 01:35:29,400
Dufayel's attempts to meddle are intolerable!

963
01:35:31,840 --> 01:35:37,560
If Amélie chooses to live in a dream

964
01:35:37,600 --> 01:35:41,600
and remain an introverted young woman,

965
01:35:41,680 --> 01:35:46,160
she has an absolute right to mess up her life!

966
01:36:19,480 --> 01:36:21,160
What are you doing, Mr. Dufayel?

967
01:36:23,440 --> 01:36:25,480
Tell me, Lucien.

968
01:36:25,520 --> 01:36:30,200
For deliveries, do you keep keys to all the apartments?

969
01:36:42,160 --> 01:36:45,880
One of your booths is out of order.

970
01:36:47,920 --> 01:36:50,360
It seems to be jammed.

971
01:36:51,440 --> 01:36:53,640
Gare de l'Est ticket hall.

972
01:36:56,360 --> 01:36:58,600
- Buy a video, get one free. - No, thanks.

973
01:37:05,120 --> 01:37:06,720
Sam?

974
01:37:07,720 --> 01:37:08,680
Samantha?

975
01:37:11,920 --> 01:37:12,880
Samantha?

976
01:37:17,600 --> 01:37:19,440
Can you stand in for me at...

977
01:37:41,000 --> 01:37:44,520
Photo booth, Gare de l'Est ticket hall, Tuesday 5pm.

978
01:38:56,120 --> 01:38:57,320
Almost done.

979
01:39:02,320 --> 01:39:06,200
The mystery man wasn't a ghost or a man scared of ageing,

980
01:39:06,200 --> 01:39:08,200
but simply the repairman,

981
01:39:08,280 --> 01:39:10,640
a normal guy doing his job.

982
01:39:12,680 --> 01:39:14,200
Sorry.

983
01:39:58,000 --> 01:40:01,240
He keeps spying on me! It's making me sick.

984
01:40:01,280 --> 01:40:04,560
4:05: Blatant female conspiracy.

985
01:40:05,600 --> 01:40:08,880
Gosh, you're tense, Georgette!

986
01:40:09,920 --> 01:40:11,400
Good luck. You'll need it.

987
01:40:16,600 --> 01:40:20,920
Excuse me. Did you put this in my pocket?

988
01:40:21,040 --> 01:40:24,320
- Yes, but I'm not the one... - I know. Where is she?

989
01:40:24,360 --> 01:40:25,840
She's at her father's.

990
01:40:25,840 --> 01:40:31,080
It's awkward. I'd like to speak to you, but... I finish work at six.

991
01:40:31,120 --> 01:40:33,000
- Can you come back? - OK.

992
01:40:34,000 --> 01:40:35,000
See you later.

993
01:40:35,080 --> 01:40:38,480
4:08: Docking scheduled.

994
01:41:09,040 --> 01:41:13,520
The blond guy in a camel coat. He's very absent-minded, too.

995
01:41:13,560 --> 01:41:15,240
How come?

996
01:41:16,200 --> 01:41:18,600
He came back three times the same afternoon.

997
01:41:19,800 --> 01:41:21,000
1:12:

998
01:41:21,080 --> 01:41:22,240
Camel coat.

999
01:41:22,360 --> 01:41:23,560
2:50:

1000
01:41:23,600 --> 01:41:25,320
Camel coat.

1001
01:41:25,400 --> 01:41:27,520
- 4:17: Camel coat. - Stop it!

1002
01:41:28,520 --> 01:41:31,600
My rash has come back! Look, Suzanne!

1003
01:41:31,600 --> 01:41:35,160
My rash is back. He's driving me nuts.

1004
01:41:35,240 --> 01:41:37,280
Lay off!

1005
01:41:37,360 --> 01:41:41,440
If she had a clear conscience, she wouldn't be in such a state.

1006
01:41:41,480 --> 01:41:43,360
I've had it. I'm going home.

1007
01:41:43,440 --> 01:41:46,800
Psychos are the last straw!

1008
01:41:48,120 --> 01:41:50,080
Georgette! Georg...

1009
01:41:51,560 --> 01:41:54,240
Stop smothering them! Women need to breathe.

1010
01:41:54,280 --> 01:41:57,400
You let them breathe, they want a change of air.

1011
01:41:57,480 --> 01:41:59,240
Fresh air's healthy.

1012
01:41:59,280 --> 01:42:01,240
Shut it, failure!

1013
01:42:03,680 --> 01:42:05,320
Failed writer, failed life...

1014
01:42:05,320 --> 01:42:07,840
I love the word "fail".

1015
01:42:07,880 --> 01:42:09,800
Failure is human destiny.

1016
01:42:09,880 --> 01:42:11,400
It's gasbag time!

1017
01:42:11,440 --> 01:42:14,560
Failure teaches us that life is but a draft,

1018
01:42:14,600 --> 01:42:18,320
a long rehearsal for a show that will never play.

1019
01:42:19,640 --> 01:42:21,920
I bet he stole that.

1020
01:42:21,960 --> 01:42:24,320
I do have some original ideas,

1021
01:42:24,400 --> 01:42:29,640
but people always steal them. A bit like your women.

1022
01:42:29,680 --> 01:42:31,600
Meaning?

1023
01:42:31,680 --> 01:42:34,760
Meaning you'd better get used to it.

1024
01:42:34,800 --> 01:42:37,200
Speak for yourself, you...

1025
01:42:37,280 --> 01:42:38,280
What?

1026
01:42:41,840 --> 01:42:44,880
- What's going on? - Nothing much. Georgette went out.

1027
01:42:44,920 --> 01:42:46,560
Joseph got mad.

1028
01:42:46,640 --> 01:42:48,080
"Went out?"

1029
01:42:48,120 --> 01:42:53,080
Just like Gina. You know who's she's with? The guy with the plastic bag.

1030
01:42:54,720 --> 01:42:57,040
I saw their little game.

1031
01:42:57,080 --> 01:42:59,320
The note in the coat pocket,

1032
01:42:59,360 --> 01:43:00,920
4:08.

1033
01:43:00,960 --> 01:43:04,760
Back he comes, and hey presto! Out they go.

1034
01:43:08,520 --> 01:43:12,040
- I'm worried for Amélie because I like you. - What do you mean?

1035
01:43:13,000 --> 01:43:16,680
By and large, the men I like are mentally unsound.

1036
01:43:16,720 --> 01:43:19,600
- I'd like to know more about you. - Ask me questions.

1037
01:43:22,320 --> 01:43:24,000
One swallow doesn't make...?

1038
01:43:25,080 --> 01:43:26,080
A swallow?

1039
01:43:27,560 --> 01:43:29,080
A summer.

1040
01:43:29,120 --> 01:43:30,440
And clothes...?

1041
01:43:30,480 --> 01:43:31,960
The man.

1042
01:43:31,960 --> 01:43:33,360
- A good cat deserves...? - A rat.

1043
01:43:33,360 --> 01:43:35,000
- Patience...? - Is a virtue.

1044
01:43:35,000 --> 01:43:36,560
- Rolling stone...? - Gathers no moss.

1045
01:43:36,600 --> 01:43:38,800
- It's a sin...? - To steal a pin.

1046
01:43:38,880 --> 01:43:40,800
Absence makes...?

1047
01:43:40,840 --> 01:43:42,240
The heart grow fonder.

1048
01:43:42,280 --> 01:43:44,160
- Not bad. - You collect them?

1049
01:43:44,240 --> 01:43:48,360
In my family, we say a man who knows his proverbs can't be all bad.

1050
01:43:52,800 --> 01:43:56,080
Pretty girl from the 5th floor, listen to this!

1051
01:43:56,120 --> 01:43:59,000
- Do you believe in miracles? - Not today.

1052
01:44:00,320 --> 01:44:02,400
You're in for a surprise.

1053
01:44:02,440 --> 01:44:05,680
What if I told you that a team of climbers

1054
01:44:05,680 --> 01:44:09,480
on Mont Blanc had found

1055
01:44:09,560 --> 01:44:14,000
hard proof that my husband loved me?

1056
01:44:45,960 --> 01:44:48,040
Lucien, I need some yeast.

1057
01:44:48,080 --> 01:44:51,800
